The PRECISION to IDENTIFY 2 POINTS is DIFFERENT
if the POINTS are NEAR the ORIGIN or NOT.

The 2 POINTS will be IDENTIFIED if
either, the 3 coordinates <= EPZERO
or      at least one of the 3 coordinates is > EPZERO and
        abs(x2-x1) <= EPSXYZ abs(x1)      
        abs(y2-y1) <= EPSXYZ abs(y1)
        abs(z2-z1) <= EPSXYZ abs(z1)
EPZERO (Default value=1e-6) is the accuracy around the ORIGIN
EPSXYZ (Default value=1e-4) is the accuracy around a NO ORIGIN POINT
